<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910116-0038</DOCNO><DOCID>910116-0038.</DOCID><HL>   Ferro Will Post Drop   In 4th-Quarter Profit</HL><DATE>01/16/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   FOE</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)CHEMICALS, PLASTICS (CHM)</IN><LP>   CLEVELAND -- Ferro Corp., a maker of industrial specialtymaterials, said it will report 1990 fourth-quarter earnings&quot;significantly below&quot; the year-earlier profit of $12.3million, or 56 cents a share, on sales of $269.9 million.   The company cited soft demand for its plastic materialsand coatings, and poor business conditions for its Brazilianoperations. Ferro said the Brazilian government's strictmonetary policy and the poor domestic appliance andautomotive markets had countered its cost-cutting andconsolidation programs.</LP><TEXT>   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,Ferro shares closed at $16, down 75 cents.   Separately, Ferro said it plans to sell its IndustrialProducts Ltd. unit in South Africa to the Royal Group ofHalfway House, South Africa. Terms weren't disclosed, thoughFerro said the sale won't have a &quot;significant&quot; value.   The company also declined to disclose the unit's revenue.</TEXT></DOC>